<br>
Lets start with some history.  This is what I've gathered of it.  EQ used to be based around battles between parties of players and parties of monsters.  The developers didn't envision single pulls as we know them today.  A player was much closer in power level to a monster of appropriate level.  At some point pulling became an art form.  This severely impacted the difficulty of any encounter.  6 on 1 isn't very interesting.  So monster difficulty was made to scale much quicker than player level.  The end result, where we are today, is that one monster has more HP than a group of 6 players and more DPS than an average group.  <br>
<br>
How does this relate?  By charming a monster at full effect you get the DPS of an entire group in one character, the enchanter.  Why can a group with an enchanter blow through a GoD trial in half the time of a good group with out a chanter?  Because you are now packing the DPS of almost 2 groups.  The Vision, as it was originaly, didn't care if a chanter took the risk of charming to gain the DPS of roughly one extra character.  That made up for what a chanter lacked in class DPS.  Compare that to now where a chanter doesn't need a group to sustain better DPS than a group.  Is charm broken?  Um, yeah.<br>
<br>
So how has that broken ability impacted the chanter class as a whole through it factoring against other upgrades it could have gotten?  I don't know, I don't play a chanter.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
How does that impact a bard?  Being able to add that kind of DPS to a group with everything else we are able to do would make us truely the master of all trades.  Can you hear the screams for bard nerf?  Dumbing down a monster's DPS while charmed isn't the answer.  Furthermore, that only insures its use as a swarmkiting tool.  I won't take the risk charming a 1500 hitting monster creates for an average warriors DPS.  Especially knowing that my charm is going to break every minute, with the good possibility that someone will die each time.  However, a swarmkiter doesn't care how much damage his charmed guy does because its all those other monsters hitting for 1500 that is creating the real damage.  His pet is there to die, the shorter he stays charmed the better.  <br>
<br>
The dizzyness effect you are describing would only enrage the rest of the pulling community.  We would have the ability to bring a monster into camp gimped up on dizzyness while no other pulling class would have that option.  That will fly almost as well as a lead balloon.  And with fade on incoming message, and a tank ready to assume aggro it could be fully managed and manipulated.<br>
<br>
So why are many bards on TCH agreeing that charm is overpowered and hope it fades away?  Because charm is broken because of the powerlevel all monsters need to be at to remain a threat under constant single pulling conditions.  TCH bards tend to care more about high level raiding, and see this overpowered ability as a threat against getting good abilities in a raid/non solo environment.  If all you care about is your ability to solo, please try out a much better ***SINGLE PLAYER GAME*** called Diablo 2.  Look Ma, no downtime!  When you are able to pull in exp at a rate equal to or exceeding a traditional group solo, you are kind of missing the point.  I hope you soon get the chance to experience EQ for what it is. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tamsindyresoul>Tamsin Dyresoul</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#330000>(6/16/04 1:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19490.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re: charm</span><hr size=1> I,for one, feel swarm kiting is actually where it needs to be at this point in the game.  And I'll say it right now:  Kudos to the devs for making it what it is.  Bored and playing at off hours?  Got 45mins to go grab some exp fast and don't want to bow out of a group right after you joined it?  Go swarm kite in, now get this, less than ideal exp zones like PoN, PoD, WW, Natimbi, etc.  You want to kill lvl 57 or lower mobs indescrimately?  Okay, go for it.  Other classes use those mobs for charm fodder as well.  Or just round up a bunch and drop a few nukes on em for the same overall result.<br>
