Please keep in mind VI/SoE, as you all know, introduced swarm kiting back in Velious of their own accord.  Back in the day, if you charmed a mob and sent it after 3 others you got 2 making a bee line for your hiney.  Yes, perhaps that was the lesser of two evils, but there you go and here we are.<br>
<br>
I, personally, have a big problem with the major assumption that, if somehow, swarm kiting is 'fixed', 'nerfed', 'broken' or whatnot we somehow, by default, get all these new charm abilities for CC situations.  I mean seriously, how long have you been playing EQ again to make that leap of faith?<br>
<br>
And that's probably my main gripe.  I've read, over the years, many folks who have advanced further in the game than myself that actually think this is some 'zero sum' kind of equation.  And I'm just not buying that today.  Swarm kiting, or single target dot kiting, keeps alot of bards playing the game and paying subscriptions.  No, it's not the 'uber' experience that AA AE kiting could be, not even anywhere near the same zip code.  But for some folks, it IS a quick fix who don't have time for 30mins forming up LDoN groups only to see the cleric back out doing laundry!  And, having played a necro who is not too far from my bard, I get to see a slower and safer experience rate as well.  <br>
<br>
I'd like to return, briefly, to charm once again.  And enchanters.  I think most of us here would agree if there was any attempt to put Bards into a hybrid situation, it would involve Enchanters.  Maybe Rogues in addition, maybe warriors.  The second part is largely a wash.  We share MANY abilities with enchanters.  And yes, I'm old enough to remember who got mana regen first <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
Having established that, I see no reason we should ever equal enchanters in the charm field.  Nor should we be more viable whenever charm is involved.  Enchanters should always have a superior charm to bards.   However, what has happened, as we all well know, is that bards can use their inferior charm 'on the run' to make decent experience by utilizing aggro rules on lower level mobs.   Enchanters, on the other hand, have more restrictions but ultimately can take down higher level mobs with higher level rewards via loot, etc. despite being restricted in other ways a bard is not.<br>
<br>
So, now we come to Omens of War.  And here we begin to see bard charms restricted by range moreso than by level.  At least, that is the word.  And I, for one, welcome that.  I will quickly abandon my range and swarm kiting mostly trivial mobs to approach the level increase and opportunity to do some old time one-on-one charming that we grew up with years ago!  The only question becomes now can I take a few beat downs between charm breaks with virtue?  I, for one, am happy I won't have to be running all over Tier 1 zones when I can go old fashioned charm fights with the higher level caps on new charm.  I'll make those chanters jealous, I promise!<br>
<br>
P.S.  Take it for what it is worth.  I'm just having fun and rambling <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
